</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Chair Tricep Dip Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">How To Do</h4>



<ol>
<li>Sit on the edge of a sturdy chair with your hands gripping the edge, fingers facing forward.</li>



<li>Slide your hips off the chair, keeping your arms straight and legs bent at a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Slowly bend your elbows, lowering your body toward the floor until your arms form a 90-degree angle.</li>



<li>Press through your palms to lift back up to the starting position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading">Tips</h4>



<ul>
<li>Keep your elbows pointing straight back, not out to the sides.</li>



<li>Avoid lowering too far to prevent shoulder strain.</li>



<li>Press through your palms to fully activate the triceps.</li>



<li>For more intensity, extend your legs straight out in front of you.</li>
</ul>



